Observing, planning and teaching group and individual music lessons for different age groups.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The aim of speciality practice II is to integrate the educational and pedagogic knowledge of students in the reality; applied form of acquiring music teaching skills the main tasks of which are to * integrate theoretical knowledge and pedagogical skills of music teaching; * acknowledge the role(s) of a teacher in a real school in its social and cultural context today; * develop self-consciousness of the student and motivate theoretical studies; * develop the perception of differences due to individuality of students in instructing their creative work, the skills to choose personal sub methodology. Observation practice at a kindergarden,  music school and elementary school: getting an overview of the work of an music teacher and of the organization of school life.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  After passing the course a student:
1.	Has an overview of the work of a music teacher with different age groups.
2.	Knows the acts and laws that regulate the functioning of schools in Estonia.
3.	Analyses the teaching and learning of music in different age groups.
4. Analyses different pedagogical situations in group lesson;
5. Creates suitable study environment for music studies;
6. Can understand individual, age-related and personal traits when preparing and analysing music lessons;
7. Analyses constantly his/her career as a teacher and plans his/her pedagogical career;
8. Involved other students and parents in planning studies;
9. Knows and practices different individual and group teaching methods.
